Nigerian rapper, Akanbi Bamidele Brett aka Cheque has announced his decision to switch from the Trap genre of music to Afropop after meeting with Wizkid. The 26-year-old ‘Rockstar’ singer took to his Twitter page to open up on how meeting with the Grammy Award winner changed his orientation about Afropop.   Sean Dampte waxes stronger as Hide Your Girls release draws…     D’Banj, Simi speak on new roles as Nigerian Idol Judges     AY welcomes second child with wife 13 years after   “I dey with wizzy, they just dey play Afro Afro so, no trap. 50 percent Afro this year, I vex,” he disclosed. Cheque, who is well-known as a trap artist, is signed to Phyno’s PentHaus music. He was one of the many breakout stars in 2020 and has continued to release hit songs.